<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.3.2-4_0002" />


<fw type="curatorial">3</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
  April 1st 1913. Well Knowe House<lb/>
  Cartnel<lb/>
  by Carnforth<lb/>
  Lancashire<lb/>
  England
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Mr. Neihard</salute>
</opener>
<p>Our friend Mr. Mosher has sent me the issue of the <title>Minneapolis Journal</title> containing your article on my work, and I should like to thank you for the sympathetic way in which you have carried it out. I was very pleased with your choice of passages to quote, and I thought they would give the reader a very fair idea of the general flavour and tendency of my verse. I also relished the hints of your critical attitude in various parts

<pb facs="nei.j4a.3.2-4_0003"/> 
<fw type="curatorial">4</fw>

  of the notice, &amp; I should be happy if, on some future occasion, you were to find opportunity in some quarter to print your point of view with regard to my work in <del>with</del> more detail &amp; at further length With many thanks for your kindness &amp; interest</p>
<closer>
<salute>I am always yours sincerely</salute>

<signed>Gordon Bottomley.</signed>
</closer>

<postscript><p>I was also much interested to look through the whole paper, &amp; to see what a fine orchestra you have Minneapolis, &amp; what a first rate performance of <title>"Die Walkure"</title> has just take place in your city.</p></postscript>

</div1>


